Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The efforts of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran to prevent a resumption of hostilities and 
fratricide in Afghanistan continue. The Foreign Ministry has 
announced that the Islamic Republic government's special envoy 
to Afghanistan, who delivered a message from President Hashemi- 
Rafsanjani, expressed the hope this morning, after meetings with 
Afghan President Rabbani, Prime Minister Hekmatyar, and other 
leaders of that country, that within the next 48 hours 
cease-fire arrangements will be implemented. 
  He added: At the meetings, the Afghan leaders expressed 
their appreciation for the Islamic Republic's peace efforts and 
their wish for an end to clashes in Afghanistan. 

